# Lambda Layer containing cryptography for Python 3.10 on Amazon Linux 2023
Build on AWS CloudShell (no Docker needed)
CloudShell runs Amazon Linux 2023 and already includes Python 3.10.
1. Open CloudShell
In AWS Console → top-right → CloudShell
2. Create layer folder
Shellmkdir -p layer/python/lib/python3.10/site-packagesShow more lines
3. Install required build tools
Cryptography needs compilers and OpenSSL dev headers:
Shellsudo dnf update -ysudo dnf install -y python3.10 python3.10-devel python3.10-pip gcc gcc-c++ openssl-devel rust cargoShow more lines
4. Install cryptography into the layer path
Shellpip3.10 install cryptography -t layer/python/lib/python3.10/site-packagesShow more lines
Optional: reduce size
Shellfind layer -name "*.so" -exec strip {} \; || trueShow more lines
5. Zip layer
Shellcd layerzip -r9 ../cryptography-layer.zip .cd ..Show more lines
Your zip file cryptography-layer.zip is now ready.
6. Upload to Lambda Layers
AWS Console → Lambda → Layers → Create Layer → upload cryptography-layer.zip.